          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1CANTMF"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Detector of Recoils and Gammas of",
                "Nuclear Reactions was used to perform a direct",
                "measurement of the 26mAl(p,g) reaction at the ISAC-I",
                "radioactive beam facility at TRIUMF."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Windowless gas target filled with H2 gas at 6.66 mbar."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Array of 30 bismuth germanate (BGO) detectors",
                "surrounding the gas target was used to detect gamma",
                "rays resulting from (p,gamma) reactions"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 27Si recoils were momentum analyzed by DRAGON",
                "magnetic and electrostatic dipole systems and",
                "transmitted to the focal plane of DRAGON."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "MCPLT",
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Recoils were identified using a local",
                "time-of-flight (TOF) system based on two microchannel",
                "plates and an isobutane-filled ionization chamber."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Positrons from decay of 26mAl were guided to",
                "the pair of NaI(Tl) detectors. By comparing the number",
                "of coincident 511-keV annihilation rays with GEANT4",
                "simulations of the NaI detector response, an average",
                "26mAl beam intensity of was determined"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Unstable 26Al was produced by bombarding a thick SiC",
                "production target with up to 70 mu-A of 500 MeV protons",
                "from TRIUMF's cyclotron and initially accelerated to",
                "energies of 150 AkeV using a radio-frequency quadrupole",
                "accelerator. This beam was then stripped to a higher",
                "charge state and further accelerated using drift tube",
                "linac."
              ]
            }
          ],
